The Aide-de-camp to Edo State Governor, Godwin Obaseki collapsed on Thursday. This happened at the swearing-in of the governor for a second term. The event was held at the Samuel Ogbemudia Stadium in Benin. As Obaseki was delivering his speech, the police officer shook for a while before going down. Security operatives rushed to his aid and took him away. His condition is unclear at the moment. Video: Obaseki’s ADC collapses during inauguration…. pic.twitter.com/XbYqSdlGFo — Ayekooto (@DeeOneAyekooto) November 12, 2020